@node Program "About the Program"

@{u}About the Program@{uu}

A year or so ago I came across a program called MassDecode that
decoded a directory full of uuencoded files.  Then I found a faster
program called UUEMaster that worked even faster.  However I thought I
could do better, so here is my attempt.

It was never going to be released but I thought 'Well after all the
trouble I put in writing it Someone may find it useful', if you do
please let me know.

Well since the last version was released I have added another 
program to interface between you, READSU and MUU.  The new program is
called muue (MUU Easy ???) and makes life a LOT simpler.

I think this is now the easiest massdecoder to install and use.  If
you disagree or think I should do something different please tell me.

I didn't get a single e-mail regarding v1.6, the first general release.
So come on - if you use this, e-mail me, if you think this is a load
of crap, e-mail me, if you come across a file you think this is failing
to decode, e-mail me... getting the idea yet??? E-MAIL ME!

@endnode
@node Features "Features"

@{u}Features@{uu}

   Ě Decodes UUencoded files

   Ě Decodes base64 encoded files

   Ě Joins multipart files

   Ě Ignores RE: subjects for faster processing

   Ě Can work on files even with no part number

@endnode
@node Warning "Warning!"

@{u}Warning@{uu}

This simplified release using muue may delete files from the 
source directory if it fails for some reason.

It will not delete any files from the workdir or destdir except 
for the temporary work files it uses.

If there are no valid files to decode in the source directory muue
will continue to delete the files it thinks are invalid or unknown.

This version will assume that if it see's a valid subject line but
with no part n/n information it is part 1 of 1 and try and decode
it as such.

All of the above will not really matter if you are just downloading
binary pictures from usenet, but if you are downloading from say a
comp binaries you may wish to run a few tests first.

I WILL NOT BE HELD RESPONSIBLE FOR ANY PROBLEMS YOU MAY HAVE.

@endnode
